        <h3><i>Introduction:</i></h3>
        <p>Jerusalem, ancient city of the Middle East that since 1967 has been wholly under the rule of the State of Israel.Long an object of veneration and conflict, the holy city of Jerusalem has been governed, both as a provincial town and a national capital, by an extended series of dynasties and states.Jerusalem is mostly important to Christianity because it is where Jesus was brought occasionally as a child, preached to the poor in his adult life, crucified at the end of his life, and resurrected by God&#128327</p>
        <h3><i>Character of the city:</i></h3>
        <p>Jerusalem plays a central role in the spiritual and emotional perspective of the three major monotheistic religions. For Jews throughout the world it is the focus of age-old yearnings, a living proof of ancient grandeur and independence and a center of national renaissance; for Christians &#127877 it is the scene of Jesus’ agony and triumph; for Muslims &#129330 it is the goal of the Prophet Muhammad’s mystic night journey and the site of one of Islam’s most sacred shrines. For all three faiths it is a holy city &#128159, a center of pilgrimage, and an object of devotion&#128720</p>
